Generic single-database configuration for personal-knowledge-base-os.

The database URL is resolved at runtime from AppConfig.DATABASE_URL (env.py), so
no connection string is hard-coded in alembic.ini.

Common commands (run from the project root):

    alembic upgrade head        # apply migrations
    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "message"
    alembic downgrade -1        # roll back one revision

The service runs fully offline without migrations (in-memory note store fallback);
migrations are only needed when persisting notes to PostgreSQL.
